Standardize the features¶

Calculate the average and the standard deviation for each variable.

In [22]:
penguins.describe().loc[['mean', 'std']].T.reset_index()
Out[22]:

Use scikit-learn to transform the features from their original scale to their STANDARDIZED scale.

We will use the StandardScaler() function to perform this transformation for us.

In [23]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

Perform the transformation following the scikit-learn "conventions" of "FIT" then "TRANSFORM"/"PREDICT".

In [24]:
# initialize the object

pens_standardize = StandardScaler()

KMeans¶

Import in the KMeans function from scikit-learn.

In [36]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

Start out with 2 clusters.

First, initialize the object.

Second, fit the object to a data set to create a MODEL.

Third, apply the MODEL (object) to a data set.

In the context of KMeans, "applying" is known as "PREDICTING" where we "PREDICT" the cluster labels.

In [37]:
# intiialize the object
km2 = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=121, n_init=25, max_iter=500)
